text:
Lexington Avenue, at the S. E. corner of East 63rd Street, showing at this location the Temple Rodolph Sholem (Followers of Peace). This structure was formerly the Beth-El Synagogue and erected in 1873. To the left is a view eastward to Third Avenue on the south side of 63rd St.

April, 1926

152 to 162 East 63rd Street, south side, between Lexington and Third Aves., showing the home of Judge Samuel Seabury at No. 154 (double-front, balcony thereon).

January 2, 1938.

George D. Chinn.
